This paper deals with energy-efficient resource management in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to computer networks and communication (cs.NI). The proposed clustering algorithm also involves machine learning techniques such as hierarchical and distance-based clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm's efficiency is also evaluated based on its computational complexity, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of the ARO-WSN algorithm in image processing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of energy consumption, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV).
